S(t) = \mu + ct - X(T)
X(t) = \sum_{i=1}^{N(t)} Y_i
\mathbb{E}[X(t)]=\mu \lambda t
\mathbb{V}[X(t)] = (\sigma ^2 + \mu ^2) \lambda t 
Y_{i} \sim N(2,9)
c=1
\mu = 20
\lambda = 1
\mathbb{E}[X(t)] = 2 \lambda t = 2t
\mathbb{V}[X(t)] = 13t
S(t) = 0
P(S(t)=0) = P(20+2t=X(t)) = P(\sum_{i=1}^{N(t)} Y_i = 20 +2t) 
